--> Project name :- OOP Wrapper

This is a simple Employee Management System project developed using Python and Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts.
The project allows users to create and manage details of Person, Employee, and Manager through a menu-driven program.

--> Features:-
- Create Person details
- Create Employee details
- Create Manager details
- Show stored details
- Exit the program safely

--> OOP Concepts Used
- Class and Object
- Inheritance
- Encapsulation
- Constructor
- Destructor
- Method Overriding
- super() function
- Getter and Setter methods
- issubclass() function


1. Person Class
Stores basic information such as:
- Name
- Age

2. Employee Class
Inherits from Person class and stores:
- Employee ID
- Salary

3. Manager Class
Inherits from Employee class and stores:
- Department

--> Menu Options:-

1. Create a Person
2. Create an Employee
3. Create a Manager
4. Show Details
5. Exit

--> Conclusion:-
The Employee Management System project successfully demonstrates the implementation of major Object-Oriented Programming concepts in Python. 
The project provides a simple and effective way to manage employee information while improving understanding of OOP principles such as inheritance, encapsulation, method overriding, constructors, destructors, and polymorphism.
This project serves as a good example for beginners to understand how OOP concepts can be applied in real-world applications.


